<subSubSection id="21F380A3B06B02244B9165047EF6EC79" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" type="notes">
<paragraph id="12816912C28A98BEC583A1C4AA506521" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B43ECEBB70C77C913C4A5853AE5C6C8" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
When 
<taxonomicName id="FEB12DE88EED15D0FF7C4FC919D6AC3C" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis id="0A22B85FD456140EDB04D5DFFA6F3FBD" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described, 
<bibRefCitation id="3A510917B82B0E0F47793E63EE592BBB" author="Ribeiro, OBC" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" pagination="145 - 148" publicationUrl="10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" refId="B4" refString="Ribeiro, OBC, Paula, CC, 2010. A new species of Orthophytum (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae) from Minas Gerais, Brazil. Brittonia 62 (2): 145 - 148, 10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" title="A new species of Orthophytum (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae) from Minas Gerais, Brazil." url="10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" volume="62" year="2010">Ribeiro and Paula (2010)</bibRefCitation>
discussed its morphological relationship with 
<taxonomicName id="52B8091F1D8FADE0C37034A660680708" authorityName="Versieux &amp; Leme" authorityYear="2007" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="itambense">
<emphasis id="7A2BF74AE5B24A0A4D9527B13421B536" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum itambense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was emphasized that these species share similar habitat, plant size, leaves, inflorescence and flower structure. Moreover, they state that 
<taxonomicName id="3075678F78CA7B6994BF0C1305D04C51" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis id="88D3AEA3915A005E8E00FD2BEF90A3EF" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="10247A2CE86DB25C2D983A7166E06160" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="supthutii">
<emphasis id="6DA2701CEA91C5823559221C2B4E87E9" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum supthutii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which was recently synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="956A6408D6079B8FF55E60A1A0A67D11" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Versieux" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="L. B. Sm." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="duartei">
<emphasis id="E716F1E8B1B8498675B976497CB56A80" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Lapanthus duartei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the same article the authors also mentioned that 
<taxonomicName id="110C726262F829A1343D38C810EE31DD" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis id="E4DE5B5E6F7EDF3A35CE6E257E007180" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be included in a different and unpublished genus proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="489364D2822CD55C3F3AB99E6FE424DE" author="Louzada, RB" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" refId="B2" refString="Louzada, RB, 2008. Taxonomia e citogenetica das especies de inflorescencia sessile do genero Orthophytum Beer (Bromeliaceae). Master Thesis, Instituto de Botanica, Brasil." title="Taxonomia e citogenetica das especies de inflorescencia sessile do genero Orthophytum Beer (Bromeliaceae). Master Thesis, Instituto de Botanica, Brasil." year="2008">Louzada (2008)</bibRefCitation>
in his 
<normalizedToken id="C32279A28F2B06FAFE026FE0F4B5F415" originalValue="master’s">master's</normalizedToken>
thesis, which later was validly published under the name 
<taxonomicName id="7A6A5519488BC6A5FD316FD8AF0BC479" authorityName="R.B.Louzada &amp; L.M.Versieux" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AE7FA4AFF26756005A90AEF74DB0E9F0" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Lapanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="720594E06161FB341CFAA94008DAE1DE" author="Louzada, RB" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" pagination="497 - 503" publicationUrl="10.1600/036364410792495908" refId="B3" refString="Louzada, RB, Versieux, LM, 2010. Lapanthus (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae): a new genus from the southern Espinhaco Range, Brazil. Systematic Botany 35 (3): 497 - 503, 10.1600/036364410792495908" title="Lapanthus (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae): a new genus from the southern Espinhaco Range, Brazil." url="10.1600/036364410792495908" volume="35" year="2010">Louzada and Versieux (2010)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DAF5B1C91B783DA6645FE4E2BE70DAF4" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Besides, some morphological characters such as the rosette shape, the morphology and size of the leaves and the size of the flowers support the decision to include 
<taxonomicName id="5ADCB728070D4977DD108E58E7A77AA8" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wanderley" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis id="304834D8BE18298D1E564442C1836EE3" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Orthophytum vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="C1A7ECCF7481E03E489D9BFDB1FED1A1" authorityName="R.B.Louzada &amp; L.M.Versieux" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E87E16158F44331920598929637F9DBF" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Lapanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
