<subSubSection id="16C71F6B4BE211713E4EFC12C1E53F4A" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2D335D8CC09CEF6728A84F2F1DFD41DE" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="47D4A9A3126F78ABA6683B5241F9A3A2" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicName id="56F4EBA2576285F07DDD23EC7850BA30" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wand." authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis id="384465B2C158722CA789C114DDA81A19" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Lapanthus vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the southernmost part of the 
<normalizedToken id="419AE30BC5500CC66331BC2C444C10E5" originalValue="Espinhaço">Espinhaco</normalizedToken>
Range, in an iron-rich region called 
<normalizedToken id="C9D58E7F67DEAFB7995007BB9EBDDCD2" originalValue="Quadrilátero">Quadrilatero</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="47C940EF772C574A5D01B3122B3AADEB" originalValue="Ferrífero">Ferrifero</normalizedToken>
(Iron Quadrangle) in the Brazilian state of Minas Gerais. Although it occurs in an iron-rich area, 
<taxonomicName id="A1BC6045ECD3337D036A6A7FEC10EA97" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wand." authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis id="85E60AFF95CCE1200CA970FDF7774D21" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Lapanthus vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found inhabiting quartizitic-sandstone rocky outcrops (
<bibRefCitation id="F6C12E9B98242F262281032C5E22CA7E" author="Ribeiro, OBC" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" pagination="145 - 148" publicationUrl="10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" refId="B4" refString="Ribeiro, OBC, Paula, CC, 2010. A new species of Orthophytum (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae) from Minas Gerais, Brazil. Brittonia 62 (2): 145 - 148, 10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" title="A new species of Orthophytum (Bromeliaceae, Bromelioideae) from Minas Gerais, Brazil." url="10.1007/s12228-009-9105-9" volume="62" year="2010">Ribeiro and Paula 2010</bibRefCitation>
) The present combination extends the genus distribution approximately 120 km southward (
<figureCitation id="93E3F4023833E8BED0EED85DF1545637" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution map of Lapanthus vidaliorum (circle), Lapanthus duartei (triangle), and Lapanthus itambensis (square)." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10175" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="B8D26DD8551B94B504EB38AAB4853E4E" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10175" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
