<subSubSection id="C50F67EBF4F79A321C5F46FF527506D9" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="36CB15F33A30F8B629D8A195864D5967" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Conservation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0473414F8A7BF1A92929FA343F829DE9" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicName id="F42DA505071398A07662935285A4347E" authorityName="Louzada &amp; Wand." authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="O. B. C. Ribeiro &amp; C. C. Paula" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Lapanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vidaliorum">
<emphasis id="67E814AA70EFACEFF9CE963F92B6CB88" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Lapanthus vidaliorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an endangered species, known only from the type-population, which is small in number of individuals, being about 3.5 kilometers from the iron ore mine Capanema and surrounded by an 
<taxonomicName id="3D8526249B463E47855EB376B23A27B1" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eucalyptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FCFE592638C96D4BA3EDEF4760D07FC2" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Eucalyptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plantation. Therefore, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="2846C44A5987F3602E721139E9BB16C2" author="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources - IUCN," pageId="3" pageNumber="66" refId="B1" refString="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources - IUCN, , 2001. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 3.1. http://www.iucn.org." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 3.1. http: // www. iucn. org" year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
criteria this species is considered critically endangered (criteria B2a).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
